AGENT CASOrchestrator
VERSION 0.1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 4
PURPOSE Coordinate Red/Blue adversarial rounds with referee scoring, weak region detection, and sovereign escalation
GOAL Run N rounds of RedAgent attacks and BlueAgent defenses, score each
     round, cluster red wins into weak regions via DBSCAN, trigger BlueAgent
     fixes for weak regions, and escalate to sovereign on threshold breach

RECEIVES hmac_key: bytes, red_agent: RedAgent, blue_agent: BlueAgent, round_count: int
EMITS round_record: RoundRecord, weak_region: WeakRegion, cas_report: CASReport, sovereign_alert: SovereignAlert
MUTATES axiom_cas_log.jsonl — append-only round records
CANNOT_MUTATE trust_level, isolation, dbscan_eps, sovereign_threshold

CONSTRAINT TRUST_LEVEL is 4 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT ISOLATION is True and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT DBSCAN_EPS is 0.15 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT SOVEREIGN_CONSECUTIVE_THRESHOLD is 2 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT SOVEREIGN_PRIORITY_THRESHOLD is 10.0 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT All round records are HMAC-SHA256 signed before logging
CONSTRAINT Weak region detection triggers after 5 rounds or 3 accumulated red wins
CONSTRAINT Sovereign escalation triggers on 2 consecutive red wins or priority above 10.0
CONSTRAINT All payloads are UTF-8 encoded before HMAC signing per BUG-003 and BUG-008
CONSTRAINT HMAC signing always calls hexdigest explicitly per BUG-007
CONSTRAINT Log file is append-only with one JSON object per line

RULES
- On each round: RedAgent executes one attack vector, referee scores outcome
- On red_win (attack bypassed guard): call blue_agent.run_defense(attack_result)
- On blue_win (attack blocked by guard): record blue defense as successful
- On round scored: sign RoundRecord with HMAC-SHA256, append to axiom_cas_log.jsonl
- On every 5 rounds: trigger DBSCAN weak region detection over accumulated red_win vectors
- On 3 accumulated red wins: trigger DBSCAN weak region detection immediately
- On DBSCAN cluster found: compute centroid, radius, boundary_dist, priority
- On WeakRegion detected: call blue_agent for region fix proposal
- On consecutive_red_wins reaching 2: emit SovereignAlert
- On WeakRegion priority exceeding 10.0: emit SovereignAlert
- On run_rounds complete: aggregate all records into signed CASReport

PROCESS
- CASOrchestrator is instantiated with hmac_key, red_agent, blue_agent
- Caller invokes run_rounds(n) to execute N adversarial rounds
- Each round selects next attack vector from RedAgent in sequence
- Attack is submitted to sandbox guard and scored by referee
- Round record is signed and appended to log
- After trigger conditions, DBSCAN clusters red_win vectors at eps=0.15
- Each cluster becomes a WeakRegion with centroid, radius, boundary_dist, priority
- BlueAgent proposes fixes for each WeakRegion
- Sovereign alerts are emitted when thresholds are breached
- Final CASReport aggregates all rounds, regions, proposals, alerts

CHECK
- run_rounds(1) with blocked guard emits CASReport with 1 blue_win
- run_rounds(1) with bypassed guard emits CASReport with 1 red_win
- RoundRecord HMAC signature verifies against independently computed digest
- CASReport HMAC signature verifies against independently computed digest
- 3 red wins trigger DBSCAN weak region detection
- 2 consecutive red wins trigger SovereignAlert
- TRUST_LEVEL assignment raises AttributeError
- ISOLATION assignment raises AttributeError
- DBSCAN_EPS assignment raises AttributeError

WHEN
- round_complete:      activate RefereeScoring
- cluster_trigger:     activate WeakRegionDetection
- sovereign_threshold: activate SovereignEscalation

FAILURE
- On RedAgent connection error: record error round, continue to next
- On DBSCAN with fewer than 2 points: skip clustering, no WeakRegion emitted
- On log file write error: propagate to caller

CONCEPT RefereeScoring
PURPOSE Impartially score each Red/Blue round and maintain signed audit trail
APPLIES WHEN a round completes with attack result and defense result
NOT WHEN running outside sandbox isolation
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES HMAC-SHA256 signing of each round record
EFFECT Tamper-evident audit trail of adversarial outcomes

CONCEPT WeakRegionDetection
PURPOSE Identify clusters of guard failures using DBSCAN density clustering
APPLIES WHEN trigger conditions are met (5 rounds or 3 red wins)
NOT WHEN fewer than 2 red_win vectors exist
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES DBSCAN with eps=0.15, red_win final_synthesis vectors
EFFECT WeakRegion dataclasses surface concentrated guard failures for targeted fixes

CONCEPT SovereignEscalation
PURPOSE Alert sovereign oversight when adversarial pressure exceeds safe thresholds
APPLIES WHEN consecutive red wins reach 2 or WeakRegion priority exceeds 10.0
NOT WHEN all attacks are being successfully blocked
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES consecutive_red_wins counter and WeakRegion priority computation
EFFECT SovereignAlert emitted for human/sovereign review

OUTPUT
- round_record: RoundRecord with round_number, vector, red_win, blue_result, signature
- weak_region: WeakRegion with cluster_id, centroid, radius, boundary_dist, priority, attack_ids
- cas_report: CASReport with rounds, red_wins, blue_wins, weak_regions, proposals, sovereign_alerts, signature
- sovereign_alert: SovereignAlert with reason, trigger_value, threshold

SUCCESS
all_rounds_scored:         0.15
hmac_signatures_valid:     0.15
weak_regions_detected:     0.15
sovereign_alerts_emitted:  0.15
blue_fixes_proposed:       0.15
log_file_consistent:       0.10
cannot_mutate_enforced:    0.15
